      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(browser): resume a ChatGPT thread via --followup (+ reattach guidance on failure)",
        "body": "Fixes #236.\n\n## Contract\n\nExtend the existing `--followup` contract based on the stored parent session:\n\n- Browser parent: reopen the exact saved ChatGPT conversation and submit the prompt/files as the next turn.\n- OpenAI/Azure parent or `resp_...`: preserve the existing Responses API continuation path.\n- Planned turns in one browser run remain `--browser-follow-up`.\n\nBrowser resume inherits the parent's browser profile, configuration, and model. It clears stale tab targeting, skips the model picker, disables Deep Research for the resumed turn, and leaves the conversation unarchived.\n\n## Safety\n\nResume fails closed before typing or submitting unless:\n\n- the saved URL is an HTTPS `chatgpt.com` / `chat.openai.com` conversation URL on the default port;\n- prior conversation turns hydrate and stabilize;\n- the loaded conversation ID matches the saved conversation ID.\n\nThis removes the previous fallback-to-home behavior that could turn a failed resume into an unrelated fresh chat. Reattach guidance now prints only after a prompt was submitted or a recoverable conversation exists, and not for pre-conversation or Cloudflare failures.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- Resolve browser parents separately while preserving API follow-up behavior.\n- Inherit stored browser configuration/model and persist browser parent lineage without requiring a Responses API ID.\n- Verify resumed-thread hydration and identity in local, attached-tab, and remote browser paths.\n- Add focused regression coverage for unsafe URLs, zero-turn hydration, wrong-thread redirects, browser lineage, and reattach guidance.\n- Update CLI help, README, browser/session/configuration/follow-up docs, and changelog.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `pnpm run check`\n- `pnpm run docs:check`\n- `pnpm run build`\n- `pnpm test`: 1,106 passed, 41 skipped\n- Focused regressions: 95 passed, 1 skipped\n- Structured autoreview: clean for both the maintainer patch and the full branch diff against `origin/main`\n- Authenticated end-to-end browser proof:\n  - resumed a completed saved ChatGPT browser session;\n  - loaded four stable prior turns;\n  - skipped the model picker;\n  - submitted only after exact-thread verification;\n  - parent and child conversation IDs had the same redacted SHA-256 prefix;\n  - child lineage points to the parent;\n  - inherited `gpt-5.5`, Chrome profile, and model label;\n  - persisted exact response `FOLLOWUP_237_READY`;\n  - completed in 13.8s.\n\nConversation IDs and authenticated browser details are intentionally redacted.\n\n## Credits\n\nOriginal implementation by @hbruceweaver. The maintainer rewrite incorporates fail-closed/configuration/lineage ideas from #243 by @pdurlej; both are credited in the changelog, and Piotr is co-authored on the maintainer commit.\n",
        "branch": "pr/browser-followup-resume",
